# OTA Update Standards (Embedded)

This document defines standards for over-the-air firmware updates: partition layout, signature verification, rollback mechanisms, and atomic update guarantees.

---

## Core Principle: An Update Must Never Brick the Device

Every OTA update must be atomic (complete or rolled back), authenticated (signed by a trusted authority), and recoverable (previous version is always available for fallback).

---

## Partition Layout

### Dual-Bank (A/B) Scheme

```
+------------------+
| Bootloader       |  Protected, rarely updated
+------------------+
| Partition A      |  Active firmware
| (Application)    |
+------------------+
| Partition B      |  Staging area for new firmware
| (Update slot)    |
+------------------+
| Config / NVS     |  Persistent settings (survives update)
+------------------+
| Recovery          |  Minimal fallback (optional)
+------------------+
```

### Partition Requirements

| Partition | Size Rule | Write Protection |
|-----------|-----------|-----------------|
| Bootloader | Minimal, fits in first sector | Write-locked after provisioning |
| App slot A | Max app size + metadata header | Unlocked only during OTA |
| App slot B | Same size as slot A | Unlocked only during OTA |
| Config / NVS | Wear-leveled region | Application-managed |
| Recovery | Subset of bootloader | Write-locked |

---

## Update Flow

### Standard OTA Sequence

```
1. Receive update manifest (version, size, hash, signature)
2. Validate: version > current? Space available? Battery > 30%?
3. Download firmware image to inactive slot (B)
4. Verify integrity: SHA-256 hash of downloaded image
5. Verify authenticity: Ed25519 or ECDSA signature
6. Mark inactive slot as "pending verification"
7. Reboot into bootloader
8. Bootloader sees "pending verification" -> boots slot B
9. Application runs self-test
10. If self-test passes: mark slot B as "confirmed" (new active)
11. If self-test fails or watchdog fires: bootloader reverts to slot A
```

### Pre-Update Checks

| Check | Required? | Rationale |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| Battery level > 30% | Yes | Prevent brick from power loss mid-write |
| Version is newer | Yes | Prevent downgrade (unless explicitly allowed) |
| Sufficient flash space | Yes | Prevent partial write |
| No active safety-critical operation | Yes | E.g., do not update during motor control |
| Network connection stable | Recommended | Reduce partial download risk |

