## Signature Verification

### Cryptographic Requirements

| Property | Requirement | Rationale |
|----------|------------|-----------|
| Algorithm | Ed25519 or ECDSA P-256 | Asymmetric -- device has public key only |
| Hash | SHA-256 | Integrity of firmware image |
| Key storage | OTP fuses or secure element | Cannot be modified by software |
| Signature scope | Entire firmware image + metadata | Prevent partial tampering |

### Verification Checklist

- [ ] Public key is stored in one-time-programmable (OTP) memory or secure element
- [ ] Private key is never on the device (only in build/signing server)
- [ ] Signature covers: firmware binary + version + target hardware ID
- [ ] Downgrade protection: version counter in OTP prevents replaying old firmware
- [ ] Key rotation plan exists (multiple key slots, one active)

### Signing Pipeline

```
Build Server:
  1. Compile firmware
  2. Compute SHA-256 of binary
  3. Sign hash with private key (HSM or secure build env)
  4. Package: binary + manifest (version, hash, signature, hw_id)

Device:
  1. Download package
  2. Compute SHA-256 of received binary
  3. Verify signature using stored public key
  4. Compare computed hash with manifest hash
  5. Accept only if both checks pass
```

