## Rollback Mechanism

### Automatic Rollback

| Trigger | Action | Timeout |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Self-test failure after update | Revert to previous slot | Immediate |
| Watchdog reset within first boot | Revert to previous slot | Watchdog period |
| N consecutive boot failures | Revert to previous slot | Configurable (default: 3) |
| Explicit rollback command | Revert to previous slot | Immediate |

### Rollback Safety Rules

- [ ] Previous firmware is never erased until new firmware is confirmed
- [ ] Boot counter tracks consecutive boot attempts (reset on successful confirm)
- [ ] Bootloader has independent watchdog (not dependent on application)
- [ ] Config/NVS format is backward-compatible (old firmware can read new config)
- [ ] Rollback event is logged to persistent storage for diagnostics

### Confirmation Protocol

```c
/* Application must call this after successful self-test */
void ota_confirm_update(void) {
    set_boot_flag(SLOT_CONFIRMED);
    reset_boot_counter();
    log_event("OTA confirmed: version %s", get_version());
}

/* Bootloader logic at boot */
if (boot_counter >= MAX_BOOT_ATTEMPTS) {
    revert_to_previous_slot();
} else {
    increment_boot_counter();
    boot_pending_slot();
}
```

