## Version Management

### Version Scheme

```
Major.Minor.Patch+Build
Example: 2.3.1+20260215

Major: Breaking changes, hardware revision
Minor: New features, backward compatible
Patch: Bug fixes only
Build: CI build number (metadata, not compared)
```

### Version Rules

- [ ] Version is embedded in firmware binary at known offset
- [ ] Bootloader can read version from both slots without booting them
- [ ] Anti-rollback counter prevents installing older major versions
- [ ] Version is reported in device status / telemetry

---

## Testing Requirements

### OTA Test Matrix

| Test | Method | Pass Criteria |
|------|--------|---------------|
| Normal update | Full OTA flow | New version running, confirmed |
| Power loss during download | Kill power mid-transfer | Resumes or restarts cleanly |
| Power loss during flash write | Kill power mid-write | Boots previous version |
| Corrupted image | Flip bits in downloaded image | Rejected at hash check |
| Invalid signature | Sign with wrong key | Rejected at signature check |
| Rollback on boot failure | Inject crash in new firmware | Reverts to previous version |
| Downgrade attempt | Send older version | Rejected by version check |
| Full flash wear cycle | 10,000 update cycles | No flash failure |

### Test Automation

- [ ] OTA test suite runs on real hardware (not just simulator)
- [ ] Power-loss tests use controllable power supply
- [ ] Corruption tests use bit-flip injection
- [ ] Rollback tests verify previous version boots and functions
- [ ] Test results include timing (download, verify, reboot)
